Makeup trial 💄. I recommend to schedule your makeup trial appointment six months out from your wedding day. This will ensure you have time to properly test out your dream look and make any changes if needed. If you're torn between two looks or want to try something a little different the second trial might help settle your nerves. Don’t forget to plan something fun in the evening so you can show off your professionally-done glam. Host a dinner with friends or family or go out for drinks. To get most out of the day try scheduling your Engagement pictures, so you get professional pictures done and see what makeup looks like during the day/ evening and how it lasts and if there any adjustments needs to be made. Don't forget to take lots of selfies 🫶

✨ Glam and Grace for the Big Day! 💍

Your wedding day is a whirlwind of emotions, and you deserve to look and feel your absolute best from “I do” to the last dance. 📸✨ That’s why we can’t stress enough the importance of hiring a professional makeup artist to stay with you for the entire day, including picture touch-ups and the reception. Here’s why ⬇️

	💫	Longevity: A makeup artist uses professional-grade products and techniques that can make your makeup last throughout the day and night, ensuring you look flawless in all your wedding pictures.
	🫦Expertise: Makeup artists are skilled in enhancing your features and know how to address any makeup issues that may arise, such as shine, smudging, or fading, so you always look your best.
	💄	Customization: Your makeup artist knows your preferences and can adjust your makeup to suit changing lighting conditions and your evolving style, creating a personalized look that complements your wedding theme.
	🥂Stress Relief: Weddings can be stressful, and having a makeup artist on hand for touch-ups means you can relax and focus on enjoying your day, knowing your makeup will remain flawless.
	📸 Photogenic Results: Professional makeup artists are trained to enhance your features for photography, ensuring you look stunning in your wedding pictures.
	🐾 Emergency Fixes: In case of unexpected mishaps like tears, sweat, or smudges, a makeup artist can quickly address these issues to keep you looking polished and composed.

Long-lasting makeup tips ⬇️ •	Start with a clean canvas: Begin with a well-prepped and moisturized face for a smooth makeup application.
	•	Primer power: Use a quality primer to create a flawless base, ensuring your makeup adheres and lasts throughout the day.
	•	Waterproof wonders: Opt for waterproof or water-resistant formulas for mascara, eyeliner, and foundation to withstand tears and weather changes.
	•	Set it in place: Set your makeup with a translucent setting powder to minimize shine and keep your look fresh.
	•	Touch-up essentials: Pack a small touch-up kit with blotting papers, lipstick, and a compact mirror for quick and easy fixes during the festivities.
